data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Same as apktool, APK Easy Tool is neither intended for piracy and other non-legal uses. It could be used for localizing, adding some features or support for custom platforms, analyzing applications and much more.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: Evildog1 XDA (APK Easy Tool), iBotPeaches (apktool.jar) Google (Android NDK tools: adb, aapt, apksigner, zipalign) Igor Pavlov (7zip), JesusFreke (Baksmali)

data.name: rebuildApiLvl.ToolTip
data.value: The numeric api-level of the file to generate, e.g. 14 for ICS.

data.name: decodeApiLvl.ToolTip
data.value: The numeric api-level of the file to generate, e.g. 14 for ICS.

data.name: label95.Text
data.value: Tip: Drop APK/JAR/Decompiled folder here. Spaces, symbols and special characters are partially supported If you got directory error, please remove them from the filename

data.name: chkAliBtn.ToolTip
data.value: Check if an APK is correctly zipaligned

data.name: installApkBtn.ToolTip
data.value: Installs compiled apk to device via adb. Make sure you do not have 2 or more devices/emulators connected If it gets stuck forever, press cancel and kill adb.exe from task manager

data.name: zipAlignBtn.ToolTip
data.value: It optimizes the way an Android application package (APK) is packaged

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Note: Apktool has no control over the frameworks once installed, but you are free to manage these files on your own.

data.name: label86.Text
data.value: Uses framework files located in a directory for decompilng and compiling. If directory is blank, it will use apk located at %appdata%/local/apktool/framework or %appdata%/local/temp

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: For the most part any apk in /system/framework on a device will be a framework file. On some devices they might reside in /data/system-framework and even cleverly hidden in /system/app or /system/priv-app. They are usually named with the naming of "resources", "res" or "framework".

data.name: label103.Text
data.value: Your work folder will not be deleted

data.name: winPosCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Remember window position on exit. If the window is out of screen, press SHIFT + Q to reset the Window

data.name: apkToolComboBox.ToolTip
data.value: Don't forget to clear framework after switching version

data.name: javaHeapSizeNum.ToolTip
data.value: Increase the heap size if you are getting java.lang.OutOfMemoryError.

data.name: decForceManifestChkBox.ToolTip
data.value: Decode the APK's compiled manifest, even if decoding of resources is set to "false".

data.name: decOnlyMainClassesChkBox.Text
data.value: Only disassemble the main dex classes (classes[0-9]*.dex) in the root.

data.name: decNoAssetsCheckBox.Text
data.value: Prevent decoding/copying of unknown asset files.

data.name: comNCcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Disable crunching of resource files during the build

data.name: chkBoxUseAapt2.Text
data.value: Use the aapt2 binary instead of aapt

data.name: chkBoxUseAapt2.ToolTip
data.value: Upgrades apktool to use experimental aapt2 binary.

data.name: decFcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Force delete destination directory. Use when trying to decode to a folder that already exists

data.name: comFcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Skip changes detection and build all files.

data.name: comCcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Copies original AndroidManifest.xml and META-INF. See more info at https://ibotpeaches.github.io/Apktool/

data.name: comDcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Adds debuggable="true" to AndroidManifest file. SmaliDebugging has been marked as deprecated in 2.0.3, and removed in 2.1. Please check SmaliIdea for a debugger.

data.name: decScheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: This will prevent the disassembly of the dex file(s). This keeps the apk dex file(s) and simply moves it during build. If you are only editing the resources. This is the recommended action for faster disassemble & assemble

data.name: decBcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Prevents baksmali from writing out debug info (.local, .param, .line, etc). Preferred to use if you are comparing smali from the same APK of different versions. The line numbers and debug will change among versions, which can make DIFF reports a pain.

data.name: decRcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: This will prevent the decompile of resources. This keeps the resources.arsc intact without any decode. If only editing Java (smali) then this is the recommended action for faster decompile & rebuild

data.name: decKcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Use if there was an error and some resources were dropped, e.g. "Invalid config flags detected. Dropping resources", but you want to decode them anyway, even with errors. You will have to fix them manually before building.

data.name: decMcheckBox.Text
data.value: Keeps files to closest to original as possible

data.name: decMcheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Matches files closest as possible to original, but prevents rebuild.

data.name: label30.Text
data.value: By default, apksigner.jar uses the values of min sdk version and max sdk version to decide when to apply the signature scheme.

data.name: zipPcheckBox.Text
data.value: Page align stored shared object files
